@startuml
title Ontology Diagram Editor - Core Event Sequence

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #405060
  LifeLineBorderColor #9AA6B2
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #F7F9FB
  ParticipantBorderColor #536475
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorBorderColor #536475
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  DatabaseBorderColor #536475
  DatabaseBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  GroupBorderColor #9AA6B2
  GroupBackgroundColor #F7F9FB
  BoxBorderColor #9AA6B2
  BoxBackgroundColor #F7F9FB
}

actor User

box "Diagram Webview" #F7F9FB
  participant "Canvas" as Canvas
  participant "Toolbar /\nProperty Panel" as Controls
  participant "Renderer" as Renderer
end box

box "Extension Host" #F7F9FB
  participant "Event Bus" as Bus
  participant "Persistence\nService" as Persistence
  participant "Document\nController" as Document
  participant "Model Tree" as Tree
  participant "Command\nRegistry" as Commands
end box

database ".odiagram\nfile" as File

legend right
  Solid arrows emit events or apply state changes.
  Dashed arrows consume events and update local UI state.
endlegend

== Open and Render ==

User -> Canvas : open diagram view
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas opened
Bus --> Renderer : render opened document
Renderer -> Bus : Canvas rendered
Renderer -> Bus : Canvas validation changed
Bus --> Canvas : display scene and warnings
Bus --> Tree : refresh model tree
Bus --> Commands : update command enablement

== Canvas Gesture ==

User -> Canvas : move / resize / delete /\nedit text / drop ontology item
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas drag started
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas drag changed\n(preview only)

alt gesture is canceled
  Canvas -> Bus : Canvas drag canceled
  Bus --> Canvas : discard preview state
else gesture is completed and valid
  Canvas -> Bus : Canvas drag completed
  Canvas -> Bus : Canvas node created / edge created /\ntext edited / elements deleted
  Bus --> Persistence : persist completed gesture
end

== Toolbar or Property Edit ==

User -> Controls : change style or field
Controls -> Bus : Canvas style changed\nor Canvas property edited
Bus --> Persistence : persist changed fields

== Persistence ==

Persistence -> Document : apply one logical text edit
Document -> Bus : Diagram document updated
Persistence -> Bus : Diagram save requested
Document -> File : save updated YAML

alt save succeeds
  Persistence -> Bus : Diagram saved
else document update or disk save fails
  Persistence -> Bus : Diagram save failed
  Bus --> Canvas : show save failure
  Bus --> Controls : keep values aligned\nwith document state
end

== Subscriber Updates ==

Bus --> Renderer : rerender from current document
Renderer -> Bus : Canvas rendered
Renderer -> Bus : Canvas validation changed
Bus --> Canvas : replace rendered scene
Bus --> Tree : refresh selection and references
Bus --> Commands : update command enablement

== Undo / Redo ==

User -> Commands : undo or redo
Commands -> Bus : Canvas undo requested\nor Canvas redo requested
Bus --> Persistence : invoke VS Code document undo/redo
Persistence -> Document : restore document state
Document -> Bus : Diagram document updated
Persistence -> Bus : Diagram save requested
Document -> File : save restored YAML
Persistence -> Bus : Diagram saved
Bus --> Renderer : rerender restored state
Bus --> Canvas : update visible diagram

note over Bus
The event bus is the boundary between event emission and event use.
Components publish domain events with payloads; subscribers update their
own state without inspecting another component's DOM or private state.
end note

note over Persistence,Document
Preview events never write the file.
Only completed, valid gestures become one logical document edit.
end note

@enduml
